Table should use the latest version of tanstack table component inside the 
The file table-defintion.js shows how it is configured with the tableDefintion json object.


Create a table component Table
Place it in a sub folder components/table


Each different column type should have it's own cell renderer component in folder renderer.
    e.g. DateCellRenderer
         CurrencyCellRenderer
When no type is specified it should use the DefaultCellRenderer


The data state is declared outside Table and passed in

const [tableData, setTableData] = useState(loadedData)

<Table tableDefintion={tableDefintion} data={tableData} setData={setTableData}/>

When selectable is true then each row should have a checkbox on the left
The parent component of the table can get a list of any selected rows (checkbox clicked).


Column Sorting
--------------

When a column in the tableDefintion object has sortable: 'true' it means this column is sortable
If a column is set as sortable, the column title should have a bootstrap arrow icon next to it
It will be up or down depending on if it sorting ascending or descending






